[Student "S"]
{NORTH has a perfect hand on which to use Fourth Suit Forcing. If South can stop 
\Ss, then 3NT would be a great contract.

There is one problem - if NORTH bids 1\S at her second turn it is NOT considered 
FSF, so she must jump to 2\S.

SOUTH, win a fine \S stopper, bids 3NT.}

